author: Sports Desk
title: PSL final will be held in Lahore: Shahbaz Sharif
text:
Share Tweet Email The packed stadiums were a sight in themselves during the group matches. PHOTO COURTESY: PSL 
Punjab Chief Minister Shahbaz Sharif on Monday gave a go-ahead to decision of holding the Pakistan Super League (PSL) final in Lahore. 
Speculations surrounded the decision taken by the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) to hold the PSL final in Lahore on March 5 after blasts in the city in the past weeks. 
Meanwhile, PSL chairman Najam Sethi while talking to a news channel said that the tickets for the epic final will be sold from tomorrow. 
Four out the five participating teams have qualified for the playoff stage which will start from Feb 28.
